[ RiPPERS C0MMENT ]

Graduating top of trance's 2012 breakout class, one incredible DJ
performance & studio production after another has, of late, seen
Bryan Kearney's career reach light speed. A man regularly credited
with twisting the codes of high-octane trance and techno into an
all-new hybrid, it's a path that's seen him progress from nu-skool
leader to A-list challenger.

Having popped his mix-comp cherry with Solarstone's ÃƒÂ¦Pure Trance V3'
last year, early summer 2015 sees the young Irish turntable-ist take
ownership of his own mix-comp marque. Incorporating his true
grit/hang-tight mixing style with a flair for the sonically
imaginative, Bryan has branded all the visceral excitement of his
label & sound into the first volume of ÃƒÂ¦This Is Kearnage'.

For its first throw-down, Kearney has drafted in fellow techno-trance
innovator Will Atkinson to share mix-duties. Together the pair
collectively chamber 36 sure-shots from the breakneck side of the
paired genres. In and amongst them are the latest from leading
propagators like John O'Callaghan, Sean Tyas, Simon Patterson and, of
course, Bryan and Will themselves. Kearnage Recordings' studio
vanguard are also standing tall, with exclusives signed right off the
mixing desks of Will Rees, Nick Callaghan, Warren Adam, Sam Jones,
James Rigby, Davey Asprey and others.

Unadulterated Kearnage from first beat through last, this is the
music your parents' warned you about! Enter Kearnage's arena from
today!

Under the hood of Bryan's disc, there's plenty of production star
wattage ready to roar. ÃƒÂ¦Adelphos' and ÃƒÂ¦Stay With Me' - John
O'Callaghan's latest respective instrumental & vocal spot rockers
arrive quick to his mix. As do Sean Tyas' ÃƒÂ¦Da Doo Da Dah' and Andres
Sanchez's psy-siding remake of Simon Patterson's Beatport-topping
ÃƒÂ¦Whites of Her Eyes'.

Naturally you're in line for an XL shot of Kearney's homegrown too,
with the upcoming ÃƒÂ¦Wake Up Call', Will Rees-collab ÃƒÂ¦Prime Example'
and UCast's rewire of ÃƒÂ¦Awaken' all dealing next-level damage. With
plenty of Kearnage Recordings' SS15 collection (Sam Jones' ÃƒÂ¦Let
Loose', ÃƒÂ¦Nethersphere' from Davey Asprey, James Rigby ÃƒÂ¦Anodise' among
them), his mix goes above the rim!

At the peak-of-peak-time, Will Atkinson's mix picks right up where
Bryan's leaves off. He nods in the direction of the sound's
forefathers, working in tracks from some proto-techno-trance
producers. ÃƒÂ¦The Code' - the latest from Mario Piu, Chris Chambers
hard-grafting rework of DJ Misjah's ÃƒÂ¦No More Mr. Nice Guy' and
D.A.V.E. The Drummer's immense, intense ÃƒÂ¦Hydrogen' all ramp tone,
tempo and temperature.

Will's own ÃƒÂ¦Fresh Meat', ÃƒÂ¦Numb The Pain' (ÃƒÂ´9/10 - beautiful enough to
bring a lump to the throatÃƒÂ¶ declared DJ Mag!), the 2015 edit of ÃƒÂ¦Game
Over' and his new Darkboy guised ÃƒÂ¦Walk The Talk' collectively send
